('Super Fantastic', 9, 'American IPA', 7, 60, 'The OG of DankHouse. This was the second recipe we ever created in our garage, and the only recipe we continue to brew today. This one is dry hopped with Amarillo, Mosaic, and Simcoe.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-india-pale-ale.jpg'),
('Sour Files #3', 9, 'Fruited Sour', 6, 23, 'This one is fruited with raspberry, blackberry, blue raspberry, grape, lemonade, and vanilla.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/berliner-style-weisse.jpg'),
('Digi Digi Digi', 9, 'Hazy Triple IPA', 10, 65, 'In the words of the great Rza.......Hoppy Hoppy Hoppy, Digi Digi Digi. Your a** will be stuck on this beer like a Victoria Secret wedgie. We dry hopped this one with Citra, Strata, and Nectaron.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/new-england-ipa.jpg'),
('Annie, Are You Ok?', 9, 'Red Ale', 5, 33, 'As smooth as that mans moonwalk! A nice and simple easy drinking red ale.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/irish-style-red.jpg'),
('Kusch Light ', 9, 'Light Lager', 4.2, 15, 'Welcome to the home of Kusch Light, the coldest and smoothest light lager there is. Here at DankHouse we’re serious about cracking a cold one and heading for the disc golf course.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/german-style-kolsch.jpg'),
('Clear Eyes', 9, 'American IPA', 6.5, 25, 'We took a new, fresh, clear headed (that part might be a stretch) approach to our American/West Coast IPAs for this one. Crystal clear in appearance and dry hopped with Citra, Mosaic, and Eureka!.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-india-pale-ale.jpg'),

('Ridge Runner Lil Harveys', 10, 'Nitro Milk Stout', 5.5, 22, 'Nitro Milk Stout with locally-roasted Ridge Runner coffee. Our buddy Pat Balding roasts organic coffee under the name Ridge Runner Coffee.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-stout.jpg'),
('Woodthrush', 10, 'Farmhouse Biere De Garde', 6.5, 20, 'It is a malty but dry farmhouse ale with a light spicing of coriander, lemon peel, and grains of paradise.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/biere-de-garde.jpg'),
('Dear Science', 10, 'Hazy IPA', 6.5, 45, 'Dear Science was the first hazy I.P.A. we brewed at Little Fish that uses a special strain of yeast, which was experimental at the time, but is now commonly accepted in the world of craft brewing.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/belgian-style-saison.jpg'),
('Smoked Helles', 10, 'Beechwood-Smoked Light Lager', 5.3, 30, 'Smoked Helles is a crisp, light lager with a moderate to intense (depending on your tolerance level) beechwood smoke character.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/vienna-style-lager.jpg'),
('Pinch Guey', 10, 'Barrel-aged Mexican Chocolate Imperial Stout', 13.5, 20, '2023s batch is a blend of imperial milk stout, aged in Heaven Hill and Basil Hayden bourbon barrels for 18 months. After blending, it was infused with whole cacao nibs,vanilla beans, ancho chiles, chile de arbol, and Cassia cinnamon.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/specialty-beer.jpg'),
('Abseil Pils', 10, 'Pilsner', 5.5, 14, 'Weyermann Barke Pilsner malt, and fermented cold with our preferred lager strain. Flavor Profile: Everything a German pils should be: elegant, simple, eminently drinkable.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/german-style-kolsch.jpg'),

('Boat Show', 11, 'IPA', 7, 10, 'Juicy tropical fruit and citrus notes blaze through this fresh and hoppy American IPA. It’s an IPA that drinks more like a strong pale ale. There is a low level of bitterness.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-pale-ale.jpg'),
('Creative Space', 11, 'Hazy IPA', 6.7, 43, 'Made with Citra, Mosaic, and Amarillo hops, this hazy IPA has an assertive citrusy brightness with some tropical fruit undertones. A couple pints of this juicy goodness will get your creative juices flowing!', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/new-england-ipa.jpg'),
('Captian Stardust', 11, 'Saison', 6.5, 33, '', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/belgian-style-saison.jpg'),
('Springer', 11, 'Golden Ale', 5.4, 15, '', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/blonde-ale.jpg'),
('Handsome', 11, 'American Brown', 5.5, 27, '', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-brown-ale.jpg'),
('MultiBall', 11, 'Pilsner', 5.5, 12, '', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/german-style-kolsch.jpg'),

('Barrel Sour Hugus Cider', 12, 'Local Cider', 6.9, 22, '2021 Hugus Farms Local Cider', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/belgian-style-saison.jpg'),
('Passionfruit Mango Gose', 12, 'Passionfruit Mango Gose', 6.5, 17, 'Tart, Crisp, and Tropical', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/english-style-bitter.jpg'),
('Tropical East Coast IPA', 12, 'Tropical East Cost IPA', 6, 27, 'Citrus, Pineapple, Juicy', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/english-style-pale-ale-esb.jpg'),
('Mexican Lager', 12, 'Mexican Lager', 5, 10, 'Light, Smooth, and Full', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/german-style-helles.jpg'),
('Kolsch', 12, 'Kolsch', 5, 12, 'Crisp, Dry, and Light', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/german-style-kolsch.jpg'),
('East Coast IPA', 12, 'East Coast IPA', 7.2, 32, 'Tropical, Juicy, and Smooth', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/new-england-ipa.jpg'),

('Tenpenny Amber', 13, 'Amber Ale', 5.4, 36, 'Balances sweet, caramel malt with a mildly bitter, fragrant hop nose. Underneath those flavors lurks a powerhouse yeast that contributes the classic ale ester profile rather than the too clean flavors in modern beer.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/irish-style-red.jpg'),
('Galactic Heroes', 13, 'IPA', 7.2, 22, 'Erupting with West Coast IPA notes of grapefruit, juicy orange and lemon, this towering beer lays it down thick and heavy without being a palate wrecker.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/themes/craftbeer2023/images/icons/beer_target.png'),
('Snake Oil', 13, 'IPA', 7.5, 27, 'We crafted this beer as the more accessible little brother to 3 MC’s with a similar hop and grain bill and using the same yeast. ', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/themes/craftbeer2023/images/icons/beer_target.png'),
('Sun-Kissed Wheat', 13, 'American Wheat', 5.4, 23, 'We started with a giant dose of wheat, a tiny smattering of hops and a classic American Hefeweizen yeast – to match those mild notes we brought along a huge helping of citrus peel and coriander.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-style-wheat-wine-ale.jpg'),
('Pioneer Pilsner', 13, 'Pilsner', 4.7, 14, 'The Germans have as many variations on the Pilsner as we do on the IPA and this one is a real classic – designed to conform to the Reinheitsgebot this Pilsner starts bitter and finishes clean.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/contemporary-gose.jpg'),
('Station Master', 13, 'Session IPA', 4.4, 31, 'A light, drinkable Session IPA, brewed clean and crisp with a shattering bitter and giant nose. You will sacrifice nothing but the hangover when you go session.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-india-pale-ale.jpg'),

('Trotwood Lager', 14, 'Lager', 4, 9, 'Fireflies flash. Crickets hum. And the campfire, around which you and your companion sit, crackles and smokes. You watch the plumes, as they slip through the arms of old-growth trees, and vanish into an expanse of ancient stars.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/european-style-export.jpg'),
('Gamma Bomb', 14, 'IPA', 7.2, 96, 'Gamma Bomb IPA. A piney India Pale Ale. Exploding with hoppy goodness. Pull the pin.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-india-pale-ale.jpg'),
('Radio Vision', 14, 'Hazy IPA', 6, 10, 'Can you see it? Can you hear it? Cut through the static and let the radio waves of Citra, Mosaic, Cascade, and Bravo hops transmit you to a hazy place filled with juicy, tropical flavors. Look. Listen. Tune in. RadioVision.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/imperial-india-pale-ale.jpg'),
('Flyer Red', 14, 'American Lager', 4.5, 12, 'Where the American spirit lives on. Flyer Red. An American Red Lager. A refreshingly smooth, patiently-fermented beer. Good things come to those who wait.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/california-common.jpg'),
('Flylight', 14, 'Lager', 4, 10, 'A solid, easy-to-drink, classic light beer. The kind that’s always in your fridge, because you know it’s good. Best enjoyed with your best buds. Fly Light Lager. Let it Fly.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/california-common.jpg'),
('Plane ole Pilsner', 14, 'Pilsner', 5.4, 30, 'Ohio. The heart of it all. The Buckeye State. And the TRUE birthplace of aviation. Take flight with a Plane ol’ Pils. But make no mistake, there‘s nothing “plane” about this pale lager.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/vienna-style-lager.jpg'),

('Mini Bomb Blonde', 15, 'Blonde Ale', 5, 25, 'Crisp, refreshing, and smooth with cereal malts; Mini Bomb is light and approachable, while not being overly hoppy, Subtle floral notes and unassuming citrus are present, but no one flavor dominates. The finish is soft, pleasant, and round. clean.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/blonde-ale.jpg'),
('Cart Path Kolsch', 15, 'Kolsch', 4.5, 17, 'Expertly hopped with Cascaxde and Amarillo, this inspired ale pays homage to its German roots while being uniquely American.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/european-style-export.jpg'),
('Hazy Miss Daisy', 15, 'New England IPA', 7, 54, 'Our traditional New England IPA boasts a tart juiciness derived from Amarillo and Mosaic hops. Featuring an inviting floral nose, Miss Daisy has noted of lemon and stone fruit with slight maltiness.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/new-england-ipa.jpg'),
('Cats in Space', 15, 'Double IPA', 10, 45, 'Crazy amounts of pineapple and mango haze with subtle pine and fruity esters send this double dry-hopped NEIPA into orbit.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/imperial-india-pale-ale.jpg'),
('Peach Please', 15, 'Kolsch', 4.5, 12, 'Infused with peach puree and expertly hopped with Cascade and Amarillo, the flavor is fruity, bright, with subtle notes of lemon.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/european-style-export.jpg'),
('Too Can', 15, 'Imperial IPA', 13, 38, 'The Imperial has a ridiculous amount of grain and an absurd amount of Centennial, Columbus, and Cascade hops which make for an ale that is full-bodied, but well-proportioned.', 'https://www.craftbeer.com/wp-content/uploads/_SF/thumbnails/american-india-pale-ale.jpg');


